  "theory": {
    "canonical_statement": "The transition between laminar and dynamo regimes in magnetohydrodynamics is organized by the magnetic Reynolds number \\(R_m=\\mu_0\\sigma vL\\). Laboratory flows with \\(R_m\\ll1\\) are diffusion-dominated, Earth's core at \\(R_m\\sim10^3\\) is near dynamo threshold, and stellar interiors at \\(R_m\\sim10^8\\)--\\(10^{10}\\) are fully turbulent dynamos.",
    "technical_interpretation": "The transition between laminar and dynamo regimes in magnetohydrodynamics occurs around R\\_m $f(\\lambda x) = \\lambda^D f(x) \\implies D omega^{2} = k^{2} v_{\\mathrm{A}}^{2}\\left[1 + \\left(\\frac{\\omega_{\\mathrm{gyro}}}{\\omega}\\right)^{2}\\right] 3/2$ 1. Laboratory flows with R\\_m much less than one are diffusion-dominated, Earth's core at R\\_m around 10\\^{}3 is near dynamo threshold, and stellar interiors at R\\_m approximately 10\\^{}8 to 10\\^{}10 are fully turbulent dynamos."
  },
